Class Category

java.lang.Object
app.categories.Category
public class Category extends Object
Represents a category from the Category Theory branch of mathematics.

    • addArrow

      public Arrow addArrow​(String name, Obj src, Obj trg) throws BadSpaceException, ImpossibleArrowException
      Adds a new Arrow with custom type to the Category.
      Parameters:
      name - Name of the new arrow (watch out for a possible LaTeX implementation).
      src - Source object.
      trg - Target object.
      type - Type of the arrow.
      inheritsDomains - if it will hold as range and image the domains of its source and target.
      Returns:
      Reference to the added arrow.
      Throws:
      ImpossibleArrowException
      BadSpaceException
      See Also:
      removeArrow(Arrow), Arrow(name, source, target, type)

    • addComposition

      public Arrow addComposition​(Arrow g, Arrow f) throws BadObjectNameException, ImpossibleArrowException
      Inserts in the category (if possible) a new Arrow result of the composition of two others.
      Parameters:
      g - Reference to the latter function g:B->C
      f - Reference to the first function f:A->B
      Returns:
      Reference to the composed arrow h:A->C, h = g(f) = g â—‹ f
      Throws:
      ImpossibleArrowException - If the two given arrows can't be composed with each other.
      BadObjectNameException - If for any reason the objects the given arrows source or target to don't exist in the category. reference to do not exist.
      See Also:
      #compose(Arrow g, Arrow f), removeArrowCompositions(Arrow)

    • addComposition

      public Arrow addComposition​(String g, String f) throws BadObjectNameException, ImpossibleArrowException
      Inserts in the category, if possible, the composition g(f)
      Parameters:
      g -
      f -
      Returns:
      A reference to the composition.
      Throws:
      BadObjectNameException - If one or both of the two functions do not exist in the category
      ImpossibleArrowException - If the composition is impossible
